Your mother has been missing for weeks.

"You don't understand, Ilemauzer of the Pit," says Auntie Grimalkin through her sobs. "No demon has ever returned from the Basilica de Sangre. The forces of... the opposition are just too powerful there.  So many demons have gone in, trying to seduce the nuns or turn them to Satan, but... they just never come back... The Infernal Powers aren't even going to try. They're giving up your mother for dead."

"No!" you shout, "They can't do that!"

"Ilemauzer! This is serious!" She grabs you, her talons sinking into the scaly flesh of your arms. You know she must be really upset. She only gets like this when she's really upset. "I already lost a sister, I can't lose a niece too! Promise me that you won't go looking for your mother!"

"I promise," you say.  But, of course, what good is the promise of a demon?

Now here you are. You look up at the towering edifice in the distance as you step off the boat, thankful to feel the stable wooden surface of the dock under your feet after so much time at sea.  Dark against the stormy night sky, the Basilica de Sangre looks like a monstrous hunched raven.  It's carved directly into the black basalt of the island, the lower levels rough and unfinished with only the occasional orange glow from a window chiseled into the stone to indicate that it's actually inhabited -- but the upper portions taper off into intricately crafted towers and spires.

You take a deep breath and steel your resolve.  Your mother is in there somewhere. And you're going to find her.

You are on a dock.
You can see a boat.
You can go east.

A wooden wharf stretches out from the shoreline into the shallows surrounding the island. You can hear the dark waters lapping against the wooden pilings below.

Your boat is moored here.
[Type HELP for guidance]
> x me

> x me
It's you, Ilemauzer of the Pit, a level 2 succubus from the outer reaches of Tartarus, right on the Gehenna border.  Hopefully, though, your disguise is good enough that no one will suspect that: your pointed ears and curling goat horns are carefully hidden inside your habit, your leathery bat wings are carefully folded behind your back, and your robes reach all the way to the floor to obscure your cloven hooves.

Still, you should probably find a more convincing body to inhabit as soon as possible.
