"Hello, Sister Ursula," rumbles Sister Hesperus as you approach. She reaches out to take your hand; it's absolutely huge, like a gorilla's hand, but surprisingly gentle. "Watch your step please, sister."

She seems to be concerned that, being blind, you might trip. But after a moment, she lets go. "Oh, sorry, Sister Ursula. I always forget that you don't need any help. Your senses of smell and hearing are just so amazingly acute! In fact, you're probably less likely to trip than any of the rest of us."
