> e

> e

You are in a secret room.
You can see Mom and a hard object.
You can go west.

Even without being able to see, you can sense something is very off in this room. The moment you step through the door, you feel a wave of repulsion. There's something here that doesn't want you here.

Even weirder, you know EXACTLY what it is.  You can see it absolutely clearly in your mind's eye. It's the large geometric design scratched into the floor, the grooves outlined in faintly luminescent paint, surrounded by a loop of arcane sigils unfamiliar to you. The design pulses with sinister power, something neither sacred nor profane but -- somehow you know -- something much, much older.  Whatever it is, it's charged with enough power to prevent you from crossing the threshhold.

Standing in the center of the design is a familiar presence -- you can't see her, but you recognize the faint smell of brimstone and the musk of unwashed fur.  It's Mom!  Unfortunately, the same power that prevents you from entering the circle also prevents her from exiting.

You also feel something hard at your feet.

> x hard object

> x hard object
It's a thick metal bar left lying on the floor where someone is sure to trip on it.
> take bar

> take bar
You grab the metal bar.
> x mom

> x mom
You don't need to see her to know that it's Mom. You can smell the faint remnants of the brimstone perfume she always wears.
> speak to mom

> speak to mom

"Mom! Mom! Is it really you?!"

Your mom narrows her eyes and peers closely at you. "Ilemauzer? Is that you?" Recognition dawns on her quickly. "By the scutes of Belpheghor, it is you! I'd recognize my baby in any body! But what are you doing here?"

"I came to rescue you, Mom! Auntie Grimalkin told me not to come, but I couldn't just leave you here!"

Your mom shakes her head. "I wish you hadn't come, Ilemauzer! It isn't safe here! Maybe you haven't noticed, but this isn't a normal convent! This island is too far away from prying eyes, and the nuns have fallen into... esoteric practices. The ocean is too close, too immediate and too deep. There's something down there, something beyond heaven and hell, something very old and very different. But whatever it is, that's what holds sway here."

She points at the circle on the floor. "Look at these sigils, Ilemauzer. They're not like anything you've ever seen before, are they?"

You squint at the sigils. They aren't the profane sigils you remember from hell, the symbols that mean comfort and protection for your ilk. But neither are they the holy signs that you find in churches or temples that humans built to exalt their beliefs in the good. They're completely unfamiliar. They fill you with a strange cold dread to behold.

"Get out of here, Ilemauzer," says Mom. "Get out of here while you still can! The last thing I want is you to fall into their hands as well!"

"I'm not leaving without you, Mom! Just tell me what I need to do to get you out of here. There's got to be a way to break that binding circle!"

Mom shrugs. "Oh, Ilemauzer, honey, I just don't know anything about this. I've never dealt with a binding circle like this one before."

"But... how do you break a regular holy binding circle? It couldn't be that different, right?"

"Ilemauzer, honey, I honestly don't know.  A normal binding circle can be broken by rubbing the ground with a combination of toadflax, skull moss and bat guano. So if you can find those three things and bring them here, I might be able to break the circle."

"Okay!" you say, "I know I can find those things! Just sit tight, Mom! I'll get you out of here!"
