> give jar to sexton

> give jar to sexton
"Hey, you look like you need some of this," you say, holding the jar of pickle brine out for the Sexton to take.

"Urgh, thanks. That's just the hang-over cure I need!" He sits up in bed, takes the pickle juice gratefully and guzzles it down.  After a moment, he shakes his head and gets unsteadily to his feet. "Aw, that just hit the spot! I feel much better now! Thank you kindly!"
> talk to sexton

> talk to sexton
"Damn, you're a big 'un , ain't ya?" says the Sexton, his eyes bulging at the sight of your towering form. "I could use arms like those out in the graveyard.  You're just built for diggin' graves an' erecting crypts. Big waste of potential to have ya workin' all the time in the scriptorium."

"Are you even building crypts now?"

"No, but you never know. You'd be just as good at knockin' 'em down when it comes time to build some replacements, I'd say."

You've never heard of anyone actually building replacement crypts. Seems kind of disrespectful to the dead. But maybe they do things differently around here.
