The Mother Superior's office is a small but adequate office, just big enough for an antique Davenport desk and a couple chairs. A large, ornate scepter hangs on the wall, above a small metal plaque.

The Mother Superior looks up from her desk as you walk in, her face a mask of fury, but her attitude softens as soon as she sees who's come to visit her.  "Well, well, well, Mr. Farkis! I gave orders not to be disturbed, but I guess I could always make an exception for a handsome, strapping fellow like yourself..."
> x Mother

> x Mother
An elderly nun with slate-gray hair and a sour look on her face, the Mother Superior is the closest thing that this convent has to a boss.  She looks like she doesn't brook any nonsense.
> x desk

