The Mother Superior's office is a small but adequate office, just big enough for an antique Davenport desk and a couple chairs. A large, ornate scepter hangs on the wall, above a small metal plaque.

Perfect!

Uh oh. You notice that the Sexton is still standing here expectantly, a lascivious grin across his face.

"Er, what are you doing here?" you say, imitating the Mother Superior's piercing, demanding voice. "I don't have time for you now! I've, uh, got a headache! And way too much work to do! Beat it!"

The Sexton shrugs. "Alright, alright," he mutters. "I gotcha, ya ain't in th' mood. Maybe later. Imma just head back to my cottage..."  He skulks out without another word.

