> e

> e

You are in a secret room.
You can see Mom.
You can go west.

You're in a small darkened room of natural stone with a large geometric design scratched into the floor, the grooves outlined in faintly luminescent paint, surrounded by a loop of arcane sigils unfamiliar to you. The design pulses with sinister power, something neither sacred nor profane but -- somehow you know -- something much, much older.  Whatever it is, it's charged with enough power to prevent you from crossing the threshhold.

"Mom! I got the stuff!" you announce as you enter the room. "What do I do with them?"

"Really? Just throw them over here into the circle and I'll do the rest!"

Apparently, even though the binding circle prevents spirits from entering or exiting, it doesn't block inanimate objects. You toss the skull, then the bottle of toadflax, then the bat guano at your mom, then listen intently. You can hear her fumbling around with the different ingredients and mumbling some obscure incantation to herself.

After a few moments, there's a sudden loud noise -- a fwoooomph of air rushing out -- and you can feel the presence of the binding circle dissipate. Your mom did it!

"Oh Ilemauzer, honey, you did it! I'm so glad, I never thought I'd be able to hold my little baby again!" cries your mom, rushing up and throwing her arms around you. "I was certain this was the end for me!"

"But we're not out of the soup yet," she mutters, releasing her grip. "We still have to get out of here without being captured. How did you get to this island, honey?"

"I came in a boat."

"A boat? Well, that's perfect. Ilemauzer, baby, I need you to follow right behind me, okay? We giong to make a break right for the shoreline and get out of here. Okay?"

You nod. Your mother pats you on the shoulder and then disappears out through the passage to the west. You'd better follow her quickly or you'll lose her again.
