You are in a hallway.
You can go west, north, east or down.

You are in a simple, unadorned hallway.  Exits to the west and east lead to the vestibule and to more hallway, respectively. To the north lies an open-air courtyard. A spiral staircase leads down to the cellarium.

"There you are, Sister Ursula!"

You feel rough hands grab your shoulders as your emerge from the cellar and the voice of Sister Magdelena hisses in your ear: "We were just about to begin the ritual, Sister! You wouldn't want to be late for the fun!"

Darn it! You forgot that you're still in Sister Ursula's body. And you can't leave her body and reveal your true form with the nuns watching!

You are roughly shoved forward and led into the cloister, where you sense all the other nuns have already congregated in a large circle. You meekly take your station in the ring -- or rather what appears to have been Sister Ursula's station.

"Finally, we're all here!" calls out the Mother Superior's voice. "Now the ritual can begin!"

The nuns murmur their agreement. You feel a sudden electric tingle in the air -- like the charge of a gathering storm but deeper and more ominous.  Something is coming.  Something is being called up from the depths.

"Oh Great Schlub! Oh Great Ancient Cosmic Horror, It of the Multitudinous Eyes, of the All-Seeing Orb! Black Toad Beneath the Hearth! Great Jazzarrdo! We have brought you a sacrifice worthy of your favor! A demon of the new ways! We consign it to you!"

Uh oh. The Mother Superior must be talking about Mom! She doesn't realize that, in fact, Mom isn't hers to sacrifice anymore; she doesn't know that you've released her and, if you could just get away, you're going to go down to meet her at the docks and get out of here!

Even without the aid of eyes, you sense... something forming in the center of the courtyard.

You are in a cloister.
You can see an abomination, Sister Grizelda, Mother Superior, Sister Heloise, Sister Hesperus and Sister Magdelena.
You can go south, east, north or west.

The cloister is a large open courtyard, paved with large irregular cobblestones and nothing above but the slate gray sky. There is a library door to the north and other exits to the south, east, and west.

> x abomination

> x abomination
A swirling mass of madness and chaos forming in the air in the center of the courtyard. Just thinking about it hurts your brain.

Judging by the chanting, this must be Schlubb of the Multitudinous Eyes, a dark and unknowable deity from the very depths of the deepest ocean trench. It would probably be a really bad thing if Schlubb actually succeeded in fully materializing in your world.
> possess Mother

> possess Mother
You jump into the body of Mother Superior.
You are in a cloister.
You can see an abomination, Sister Grizelda, Sister Heloise, Sister Hesperus, Sister Magdelena and Sister Ursula.
You can go south, east, north or west.

The cloister is a large open courtyard, paved with large irregular cobblestones and nothing above but the slate gray sky. There is a library door to the north and other exits to the south, east, and west.

The Mother Superior pauses in her chanting as you enter her body.  You blink stupidly at the crooked scepter in your grip.  Better do something with that before the other nuns notice you've stopped chanting.
> throw scepter

> throw scepter
You throw the scepter...

It lands in the middle of the swirling mass...

Kaboom! There's a flash and smoke fills the cloister...  An awful screeching sound fills the air and a gust of hot, stinking wind nearly knocks you off your feet.  All around you, the nuns break their circle, shouting in confusion as they scatter.

When the smoke clears, all is quiet...

The sisters and the abomination have gone...

Can this really be over? ...

Well almost.  You've ruined the ritual, but it probably won't be long before the nuns recover their senses enough to come after you.  Better catch up with Mom and escape the island before they come back!
